<br>
Other then Elemental, wizards tend to shave off about 15-30 minutes per AA soloing vs. what they can get in a group of people with equivelent gear.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Per unit mana, a wizard can do twice (or more) as much damage solo as they can grouped.<br>
<br>
Lets take a group of 6 wizards, with a slow/cheal/tank team power leveling them.  This should get better XP than a group of people in &quot;equivilent&quot; gear.<br>
<br>
If X is the amount of damage a wizard can do with nukes in 1 hour, and M is the amount of HPs a mob has, and Y is how much XP each mob is worth. . .<br>
<br>
Over 1 hour, they do 6 * X damage.  This kills 6X/M mobs. <br>
<br>
Each wizard earns 6/5 XY/M xp over that hour.<br>
<br>
The group then leaves, and 1 wizard remains behind.  This wizard proceeds to quad for an hour.<br>
<br>
Over that hour, he does 2 * X damage.  This kills 2X/M mobs.<br>
<br>
He earns 2 XY/M xp.<br>
<br>
Notice that 2 XY/M is almost twice 6/5 XY/M.<br>
<br>
It is even worse than that, however.  Due to the &quot;holy trinity&quot; of crappy damage dealers needed to mitigate PoP damage output, there are usually only 3.5-4 damage dealers in a group (tank = 1/2 damage dealer, healer is busy, and slower/buffer).  Which makes the comparison on the side of the soloer even more massive.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, the soloing wizard gets fewer med ticks, which cuts down on her xp by a decent %.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying good wizards don't group.  I'm saying that the better the wizard, the larger the draw<br>
<br>
The ways in which a group can beat out a quadding wizard:<br>
1&gt; The group has damage dealers who far far outdamage the wizard.<br>
2&gt; They mobs they are killing have a far better XP / HP ratio than what the wizard can quad.<br>
<br>
In the case of 1, the wizard is gimping the group.  If they dropped the wizard, they would earn xp faster more than likely.<br>
<br>
I must assume you know sweet spots that fit catagory 2.  However, if you haven't noticed, most players in the game seem to XP on basically quaddable mobs, as sad as that is.  And, the XP / HP ratio has to twice that which a wizard can pull off.<br>
<br>
After the change on test, the group of 6 wizards being PL'd will earn 2.16 XY/M, MORE than the quadding wizard.<br>
<br>
Good wizards are great in a group.  But, a random LFG wizard is more likely to be a gimp than a random LFG other damage dealing class, simply because the game mechanics provide such a massive incentive to solo.  I've seen it first hand.<br>
<br>
The biggest remaining problem is the holy trinity pigeonhole problem.  A group wants 1 and exactly 1 (cleric slower plate) -- and if there are more pigeons than pigeonholes, people are stuck LFG or soloing.<br>
<br>
Slowers have it the best -- all but 1 slower class has a good backup role they perform superbly at (enc: charm damage + buffs + cc, bard: cc + songs, bst: damage + spirit buff).<br>
<br>
Druids are half as good as a cleric at healing.  Shamans are 75% to 30% as good a healer as a cleric (depending on exact situation).  Clerics are only truely effective in a full group behind a plate tank.<br>
<br>
Plate tanks don't stack -- a 2nd tank doesn't help the group xp better, unless things go wrong.<br>
<br>
If they put what they described on test, and got to work on the remaining problem, things will be better.<br>
