<br>
In response to your question about whether the designers just didn't forsee quadding...  <br>
<br>
I was quadding stuff 5 years ago in beta 1 before half of the original mainland was even online and it was a pretty cool day when 80 people were online total.<br>
<br>
I did this in front of Brad McQuaid and several of the lead designers at the time.  <br>
<br>
Quadding changed a lot during beta, swinging wildly from very easy to very hard and about everything in between as they changed spells around a lot, and you needed someone to cast SoW on you (no potions, no jboots early on), but it was definately demonstrated as possible.<br>
<br>
Heck, at one point aggro was so predictable that two wizards could &quot;AE Pingpong&quot; mobs and never get hit.. was kinda fun.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the dev team definately knew about soloing &amp; quadding, and they never considered it out of line based on downtime between quads and the risk factor.<br>
<br>
Quadding only became a problem when other classes started bitching about it really.. and more recently with the insane exp available to quadders in some of the higher tiered PoP planes.<br>
